    <h2 class="anima-grow">
        <i class="fab fa-css3-alt fa-lg color-violet"></i> 
        CSS Variables
        <i class="fas fa-glass-whiskey fa-lg color-violet"></i>
    </h2>

    <header class="head">
        Animadio use CSS Variables for overloading possibility, 
        the only thing to do is to overload the Variable you want 
        in your style.css file !
    </header>

    <section>
        <h3>How to overload a CSS Variable ?</h3>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>
                You need first to choose a 
                <b class="color-violet">Selector</b> :
            </p>
            <code><span 
            class="color-yellow">:root</span></code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Then, the 
                <b class="color-violet">CSS Variable</b> 
                to overload :
            </p>
            <code><span 
            class="color-blue">--white</span></code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Finally, the 
                <b class="color-violet">Value</b> 
                you want to put in the Variable :
            </p>
            <code><span 
            class="color-orange">#fff</span></code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                You will have this result for this 
                <b class="color-violet">Example</b> :
            </p>
            <code><span 
            class="color-yellow">:root {</span> <span 
            class="color-blue">--white</span><span 
            class="color-grey">:</span> <span 
            class="color-orange">#fff</span> <span 
            class="color-yellow">}</span></code>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </section>

